1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:01,840
I dropped my car key into this pond.

2
00:00:02,160 --> 00:00:04,040
I guess you need to take responsibility.

3
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:05,440
This is my personal contact.

4
00:00:05,640 --> 00:00:06,600
Would it be alright if I contact you romantically?

5
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:07,680
Be my guest.

6
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:11,000
Will you marry me?

7
00:00:11,160 --> 00:00:11,760
Yes, I will.

8
00:00:12,040 --> 00:00:12,600
Crap!

9
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:13,240
Hey.

10
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:15,840
You need to take your shirt off.

11
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:17,040
You don’t want to get sick, do you?

12
00:00:17,240 --> 00:00:20,640
When did you know
you wanted to marry Tim?

13
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:23,640
I just know I want to be with him every day.

14
00:00:24,520 --> 00:00:25,720
Will you marry me?

15
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,360
JEERAMONGKOLTHANUN

16
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:28,440
Ten billion?

17
00:00:32,560 --> 00:00:34,240
PLAY WITH HIS FEELINGS,
NOT YOUR OWN.

18
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:36,240
DO NOT THINK PAI IS CUTE!

19
00:00:41,560 --> 00:00:43,600
DO NOT FALL FOR THE TARGET
AT ALL COSTS!

20
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:49,920
Why should you hold back?

21
00:00:50,120 --> 00:00:51,280
We’re going to be married soon.

22
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:53,400
To hell with it, then.

23
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,360
Do not fall for your target.

24
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:14,000
Hello?

25
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:15,040
Oom?

26
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:17,080
Are you free tomorrow?

27
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:19,240
I have a job for you.

28
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:21,360
Alright.

29
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:37,280
I’m here to officially ask for
Pai’s hand in marriage to Tim.

30
00:01:42,440 --> 00:01:44,160
It’s a pleasure.

31
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:47,480
We have all seen how consistent Tim is.

32
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:49,560
We have no objection at all.

33
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,080
That’s right.

34
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:54,480
Isn’t that right, honey?

35
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,440
Thank you, Grandpa, and also
Papa and Mama.

36
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:01,280
I am so grateful to hear that,

37
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:04,280
especially after listening to Tim
bragging about Pai all the time.

38
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:08,160
When they started dating,
Tim called me every day

39
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:11,480
asking about how his father used to
woo me when we were falling in love.

40
00:02:11,480 --> 00:02:12,880
He thought he’d use the same trick, I believe.

41
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:16,800
Really?

42
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:19,840
Maybe a little.

43
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,160
Let me get some for you.

44
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:25,520
Here, Mom.

45
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:26,840
Thanks, love.

46
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:28,360
But you don’t have to worry about me.

47
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:29,800
You should take care of Pai.

48
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:32,080
Excuse me. Can we have a fork?

49
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:36,480
Auntie, Da Zhan is a grownup now.

50
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:39,280
Why don’t you let him try using chopsticks
so he can finally use them?

51
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:43,120
Oh, don’t you berate your cousin when
you have a boyfriend who does it for you.

52
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:45,880
I’ll get some food for him.

53
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:47,960
What do you want, Da Zhan?

54
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,080
Har gow, please.

55
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:49,480
Okay.

56
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:51,240
Uh…

57
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:54,760
There you go.

58
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:55,880
Thank you.

59
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:58,560
Maybe I can teach you
how to use chopsticks later?

60
00:02:59,040 --> 00:02:59,600
Nah.

61
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:00,800
No?

62
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:09,920
Here.

63
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,360
You’re giving me both fish collars?

64
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:15,280
Let me share one with you.

65
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,200
Thank you.

66
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:25,040
I’ll give you two more next time.

67
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:50,800
I’m really sorry I can’t go with you today.

68
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,640
Oh, it’s alright, love.

69
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,040
You should spend time with your family.

70
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:56,400
I’m already so happy today.

71
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:57,760
I am overjoyed.

72
00:04:58,360 --> 00:05:00,320
I’ll be smiling all the way back to London.

73
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:05,240
If Tim is ever bothersome,
you have to let me know, love.

74
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:06,280
Of course.

75
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,040
You’re going to be in trouble.

76
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,440
Mom.

77
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:12,720
Don’t you think it’s too soon to love Pai
more than your own child?

78
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,680
What’s not to love about him, am I right?

79
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:18,680
Safe travel, Mom.

80
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:19,040
Of course.

81
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:20,360
I have to go for now.

82
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:22,400
I’ll see you later.

83
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:32,320
Are you sure you’re alright?

84
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:33,720
Umm.

85
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,520
Everyone seems like
they’re in a good mood today.

86
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,440
I don’t think there’ll be any cause
for headaches.

87
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:40,320
Call me if something happens.

88
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,040
Do not bottle it up all alone, you hear me?

89
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:45,120
Just go.

90
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,040
Your mother is waiting.

91
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,320
Bye, then.

92
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:51,920
Tim!

93
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,320
It’s too bad.

94
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:21,960
If I wasn’t playing a rich lady today,

95
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:25,320
I would have asked them to pack up
some of that mushroom soup for me.

96
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,160
Good job today, Mama.

97
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,160
And to think that was all unrehearsed.

98
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,560
As expected of
the number one in the industry.

99
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:32,680
Of course.

100
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:36,440
In this line of work,
you need to be ready to take on any role.

101
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:38,400
You do remember
what you said to them, though?

102
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,560
You’ll meet them again
at the wedding, you know?

103
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:44,720
Oh, I’m sure rich people don’t pay
any mind to every single small detail.

104
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:46,560
Aunt Kia remembers everything.

105
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:52,640
But that Pai kid is adorable, though.

106
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:57,640
And I notice that Mr. Soepohn
smiles with his eyes when he talks to you.

107
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:59,200
He seems to really adore you.

108
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,400
Of course, he does.

109
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,560
That’s the point of this whole scam.

110
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:06,760
Honestly, though.

111
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:11,360
Why don’t you just fall in love properly
and spend your life with him?

112
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,680
I’d be insane to do that.

113
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,960
If this whole thing ever came out,

114
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,920
people like them would
totally have me ruined.

115
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:20,720
It’s a shame, you know.

116
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,880
You two have chemistry.

117
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:25,720
Here is your paycheck.

118
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:29,800
Fabulous.

119
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:30,520
Thanks.

120
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:31,640
- Bye.
- I’m off.

121
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,200
How is North doing?

122
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,200
Did he start working at the office?

123
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,520
I’m still trying to coax him into it.

124
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,840
You know how stubborn he is, Grandpa.

125
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:56,560
Pai.

126
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:58,920
North is a poor kid.

127
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:04,480
I would never die happy
if I didn’t see him get his life together.

128
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:07,320
He’s one of us, Pai.

129
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:09,600
We can’t simply abandon him.

130
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,400
Of course, Grandpa.

131
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:15,960
Goodnight.

132
00:08:33,040 --> 00:08:33,840
(Hi, baby.)

133
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:36,160
Did you leave the airport?

134
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:38,280
(I’m still at the airport, actually.)

135
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:40,280
(Do you need me to pick you up?)

136
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:41,040
(I can leave right away.)

137
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:43,480
It’s alright.

138
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:45,840
You should spend time with your mother.

139
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:47,800
I’ll have a chauffeur drive me home.

140
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:48,760
Alright.

141
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,560
I’ll see you when I’m done here.

142
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:52,240
Bye.

143
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:05,080
You lie with a more straight face
than a lawyer like me, dude.

144
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:07,080
I mean, I’d make a good lawyer.

145
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,680
I could defend some criminals and steal your job.

146
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:10,360
Nope.

147
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:11,480
I won’t allow it.

148
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:13,520
If you stole my job,
how the hell would I feed myself?

149
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:15,200
On shaved ice, apparently.

150
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,360
And it’s good, too.

151
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:23,360
But why don’t you hurry home
and keep up the scores with Pai?

152
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:25,240
Listen, dude.

153
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:27,960
I know when Pai needs me,

154
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:30,120
but I won’t let him get his way every time.

155
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:33,400
This will keep him wanting me more and more,

156
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,600
and doesn’t take me for granted.

157
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,440
Sounds cool.

158
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:40,280
But that’s a useless tactic for a lawyer.

159
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:42,960
Use your brain sometimes.

160
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:43,600
Hey.

161
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,120
It’s late.

162
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:49,400
I have to meet Airy tomorrow.

163
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,040
Sure.

164
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:56,280
But do think of Attorney Prem here
when your scheme falls apart.

165
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:57,440
Don’t jinx me like that.

166
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,200
You want me to tip the shaved ice
over your pants, dude?

167
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,280
Don’t waste food like that!

168
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,160
Gotta go.

169
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,200
- See ya.
- Good luck.

170
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:13,760
Hello, sir.

171
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,560
Same table?

172
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:16,400
Yes.

173
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:17,440
Welcome.

174
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:26,680
Hong.

175
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:28,440
Airy, hello.

176
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:29,360
Sit down.

177
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:32,880
Hi there.

178
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:34,720
Oh, Hong.

179
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:35,160
Yes?

180
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:36,360
You’re sitting so far away from me.

181
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:37,880
It’s like you don’t even miss me.

182
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:41,720
I just want to make sure you’re comfortable
in your seat, of course.

183
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:47,960
Shall we try something new or
should I order your favorite dish?

184
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,800
I want to try something new…

185
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:52,640
Oh?

186
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:53,640
Like you, Hong.

187
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,040
Not only are you beautiful,

188
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:01,160
but also funny.

189
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,040
Of course.

190
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:08,000
I spent a hundred thousand on you, I don’t
intend to just hold hands, you know?

191
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:12,600
Airy, but you said I’m not like
your other sugar babies?

192
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,480
You have to win me over first, remember?

193
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,360
Aren’t you a charmer?

194
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:21,160
I love it.

195
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:24,080
Right.

196
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:25,880
What would you like?

197
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:35,560
IN LOSSES

198
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:52,160
He did not make one bit of profit since day one?

199
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:53,840
How come the place didn’t go out of business already?

200
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:57,000
I was told Mr. North tided it over out of his own pocket.

201
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,440
So much for ‘learning business by himself.’

202
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:05,360
If it went on like this, he wouldn’t learn
anything even in 10 years.

203
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:12,480
Unreachable yet again.

204
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,560
Bring him here right away, Nana.

205
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:15,560
Of course, sir.

206
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:35,640
You’re still busy?

207
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:36,640
I’ll wait outside.

208
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:37,440
You can stay, Tim.

209
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:39,440
We’ll only be a minute.

210
00:12:41,520 --> 00:12:42,640
Just confess.

211
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:44,200
You know you can’t hide it from me.

212
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,560
Y–You…

213
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:49,720
You know?

214
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,000
Nana told me everything.

215
00:12:57,880 --> 00:13:00,080
It was my fault for not telling you
before I went ahead with it.

216
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:02,880
But…

217
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:07,680
I want you to be happy for me and my new relationship.

218
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:10,840
MARRIAGE CERTIFICATE

219
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:12,600
What?!

220
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,280
- What?
- What?

221
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:21,600
MARRIAGE CERTIFICATE

222
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:25,720
But who is…

223
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:29,160
Who is this Issara Preechajit guy?

224
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:09,600
Alright.

225
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:10,920
Whatever happens,

226
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:12,800
at least I have some cash on me.

227
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:40,760
My boy…

228
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:43,680
We’re going to be filthy rich!

229
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,880
NORTH

230
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:02,600
Hello, North?

231
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:03,720
(U, hi.)

232
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,840
(Are you busy right now?)

233
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:07,760
(There happens to be an emergency.)

234
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,040
Oh.

235
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:26,400
Pai, please calm down—

236
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,080
Who are you?

237
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,760
Where are you from? How old are you?
What do you do for a living?

238
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:31,440
Why did you marry my cousin without telling his family?

239
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:31,920
Huh?

240
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:34,800
Calm down.

241
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,040
How can I calm down?

242
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,560
North, what were you thinking?

243
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:38,680
Were you drunk?

244
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:40,720
Call Attorney Vicha and we’ll get you divorced right now!

245
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:42,280
Divorce? I’m not getting a divorce!

246
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:45,320
This is exactly why I had to
get married without telling you, Pai!

247
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:45,960
You certainly did!

248
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:47,120
I’m a grown man!

249
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,560
I can think for myself!

250
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:51,760
If that’s the case, then tell me who he is
and how come you’re married to him!

251
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:52,760
Well, I…!

252
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:56,000
I don’t know.

253
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:58,200
- North!
- Calm down, baby!

254
00:15:58,320 --> 00:15:59,280
Pai, calm down.

255
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:01,800
Uh, North and I met when we went hiking.

256
00:16:02,120 --> 00:16:03,520
We were lost in the woods together for a night.

257
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:05,360
We thought we wouldn’t make it.

258
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:07,520
But that night was beautiful. It really was.

259
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:11,400
I knew right away that
I found the right person for me.

260
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:12,760
I didn’t want to waste any more time.

261
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:13,480
“Waste time”?

262
00:16:13,680 --> 00:16:16,760
You think getting to know him
and meeting his family is a waste of time?

263
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:18,120
I told him not to!

264
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:19,800
But if you want to, Pai—

265
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:20,520
That’s Mr. Pai to you!

266
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:22,880
Mr. Pai.

267
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:27,200
If you want to know me better, Mr. Pai,
I can tell you everything about myself.

268
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:29,800
I’ll go and pay my respect to North’s grandfather, too.

269
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:35,880
Pai.

270
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:38,480
Grandpa and everyone else can’t know about this.

271
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:39,960
Attorney Vicha as well.

272
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:41,960
Why not?

273
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:45,800
Imagine what would happen if Aunt Kia found out.

274
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:50,040
It’s best we deal with this ourselves,
don’t you think so?

275
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:01,760
Don’t tell anyone about this until I approve of it.

276
00:17:04,120 --> 00:17:04,800
As for this.

277
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:07,240
Divorce is still an option.

278
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,240
Don’t think you can make
any demands from my cousin!

279
00:17:10,360 --> 00:17:11,000
Do you hear me?

280
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:13,880
Of course, Mr. Pai.

281
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:32,400
I’m going to the bathroom.

282
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:33,400
Of course.

283
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,160
It’s over there.

284
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:34,680
Right.

285
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:37,800
Are you alright?

286
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:38,720
Are you okay?

287
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:39,800
I’m sorry.

288
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:42,800
I was in a hurry and didn’t see you there.

289
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:43,680
I’m sorry.

290
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:44,560
It’s alright.

291
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:47,480
I’ll be a minute.

292
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:48,920
I’ll wait outside.

293
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:02,240
You dropped this.

294
00:18:03,680 --> 00:18:04,360
I found it.

295
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:06,880
Oh, thank you.

296
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:11,280
You’re forgetful, aren’t you?

297
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:14,320
Excuse me?

298
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:21,200
Do you know what the number
at the bottom of the card means?

299
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:28,640
Are you okay?

300
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:29,760
Are you alright?

301
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:35,720
This number indicates how many times you have a new card issued.

302
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:37,880
And yours says…

303
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:39,680
Wow.

304
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:42,280
19 times.

305
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:46,120
If it’s not because you’re forgetful,

306
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,320
why else would it be?

307
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:01,640
I’m sure I didn’t drop my wallet.

308
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:08,640
For you to pick my pocket so easily
when you bump into me like that…

309
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:12,440
Do you usually ‘find’ a lot of wallets?

310
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:31,640
HEY, LOOK INTO THIS GUY FOR ME.

311
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:41,920
I’m sorry, sir.

312
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:43,000
Nana.

313
00:19:43,280 --> 00:19:45,000
Look U up for me.

314
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:48,320
If there’s any suspicion that he could
be using North, let me know.

315
00:19:48,480 --> 00:19:49,360
Of course, Mr. Pai.

316
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:55,120
Ah. Excuse me.

317
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:05,400
Come here.

318
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:19,120
I don’t understand North.

319
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:21,200
What was he thinking to marry a total stranger?

320
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:25,120
You should be nice to him.

321
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:28,360
Are you taking his side?

322
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:29,720
Of course not.

323
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:32,040
I just want you two to talk nicely.

324
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:34,760
So your eyebrows don’t have to
work overtime like this.

325
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:36,840
I know.

326
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:46,120
Mr. Pai!

327
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:49,680
Nana.

328
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:51,680
I told you to knock.

329
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:54,200
I wanted to ask about the papers
you need for today’s meeting.

330
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:55,480
But I can come back later, sir.

331
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:18,160
I think this room is big enough for two people.

332
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:22,680
The kitchen is over there.

333
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:24,160
I barely use it.

334
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:26,000
The bathroom is beyond that.

335
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:29,120
I see.

336
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:32,520
This is all your stuff?

337
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:37,280
Oh, yes. This is everything.

338
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:38,360
I travel light.

339
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:42,360
Shall we take a look at the bedroom?

340
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:43,480
Okay.

341
00:21:51,520 --> 00:21:54,200
This is my bedroom.

342
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:55,880
Oh, I see.

343
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,000
It’s big.

344
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:02,360
Which side of the bed do you usually sleep on?

345
00:22:03,040 --> 00:22:04,200
I sleep in the middle.

346
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:08,040
But you can let me know which side you prefer.

347
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:09,240
I’m okay with anything.

348
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:10,480
I sleep in the middle as well.

349
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:11,640
Oh?

350
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,160
How about this?

351
00:22:16,320 --> 00:22:17,240
Oh, U.

352
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:35,760
What’s wrong?

353
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:37,680
What are you thinking?

354
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:40,400
No, it’s just…

355
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:45,120
I’m thinking about what Pai said today.

356
00:22:47,520 --> 00:22:50,000
I couldn’t answer any of his questions.

357
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:57,240
Maybe I really don’t know you well enough.

358
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:04,360
North.

359
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:11,000
Why don’t we get to know each other right now?

360
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:17,040
How fast we go… I’ll let you set the pace.

361
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:34,200
Good idea!

362
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:37,080
Let’s go on a date!

363
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:44,760
Date?

364
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:45,760
Yeah!

365
00:23:57,440 --> 00:23:58,280
U.

366
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:05,040
What is that?

367
00:24:06,640 --> 00:24:07,680
What are you hiding?

368
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:14,280
Here.

369
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:16,920
What is that?

370
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:17,920
You’ll know soon.

371
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:22,080
I have a plan for our date, though.

372
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:24,360
I only need one hour.

373
00:24:27,680 --> 00:24:28,320
Alright.

374
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:29,120
Good.

375
00:24:33,560 --> 00:24:34,200
Please.

376
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,040
Thank you.

377
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,480
Let’s put on a seat belt for your safety.

378
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:15,760
You ready?

379
00:25:16,920 --> 00:25:18,000
For a while now.

380
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:20,600
Let’s go.

381
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:45,880
Come on.

382
00:25:57,040 --> 00:25:58,120
Move your legs.

383
00:26:05,040 --> 00:26:06,040
Is there a hole in the middle
of your racket or something?

384
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:08,040
I’m gonna get serious now.

385
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:08,560
Alright.

386
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:14,760
North, you.

387
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:15,480
Yes?

388
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:17,560
Is that the best you can do, U?

389
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:32,080
Are you tired?

390
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:49,000
Breathe in and breathe out.

391
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:56,080
Honestly.

392
00:26:57,160 --> 00:26:58,520
Not counting the hike,

393
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:02,440
this is the most exhausted I’ve been.

394
00:27:03,840 --> 00:27:04,840
Did you have fun, though?

395
00:27:05,760 --> 00:27:06,720
I did.

396
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:13,440
But I thought we were getting to know each other.

397
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:16,840
We’re doing that through sports.

398
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:20,960
You’re strong-willed.

399
00:27:21,360 --> 00:27:22,920
You believe in your own strategies.

400
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:25,400
When under a lot of pressure,

401
00:27:25,760 --> 00:27:28,360
you let go of everything and just wing it.

402
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:29,240
Am I right?

403
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:36,480
What about you?

404
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:37,240
Did you get anything on me?

405
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:41,240
Can we try again?

406
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:43,400
My eyes were only on the ball.

407
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:45,280
You’re so amazing.

408
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:47,080
You were playing and analyzing and still won.

409
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:48,600
Did you use to be an athlete?

410
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:50,600
No.

411
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:55,200
It’s just my mother taught me how to read people.

412
00:27:57,120 --> 00:27:58,040
That must be nice.

413
00:27:58,280 --> 00:28:01,280
I only got to live with Pai and Grandpa.

414
00:28:02,040 --> 00:28:03,800
They never taught me anything.

415
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:06,080
All they did was scold and scold and scold me.

416
00:28:06,720 --> 00:28:09,520
Sometimes I wonder,
if I’m so much trouble for them,

417
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,480
why won’t they just leave me alone?

418
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:12,400
Oh, North.

419
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:13,560
Don’t say that.

420
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:15,520
I’m sure they do it out of love.

421
00:28:20,040 --> 00:28:21,720
You’re so optimistic, U.

422
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:24,760
You must have such a lovely family.

423
00:28:37,720 --> 00:28:39,600
Can I meet your family?

424
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:43,200
Uh…

425
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:51,960
I rented the same house.

426
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:56,280
Remember, you’re a single mom
who works as an accountant.

427
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:57,760
When I was in school,

428
00:28:58,320 --> 00:29:01,040
I was on scholarship
because I wanted to help financially.

429
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:02,200
Also…

430
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:05,400
I believe in love at first sight.

431
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:09,120
How does that have to do with anything?

432
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:12,120
I’m sure an amazing actor like you
will find a way to fit it into a conversation.

433
00:29:12,240 --> 00:29:13,480
Don’t screw up, Mama.

434
00:29:14,120 --> 00:29:16,360
This guy is my retirement plan.

435
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:19,240
As if I ever screw up.

436
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:20,520
But let’s talk about you.

437
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:22,200
Did you clean things up on your end?

438
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:23,640
On my end?

439
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:25,240
Nart, duh.

440
00:29:25,360 --> 00:29:26,920
She just got out of jail.

441
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:30,520
If she knew you caught such a big fish,

442
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:32,560
I don’t think she’d go down without a fight.

443
00:29:33,920 --> 00:29:35,840
In my entire career,

444
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:39,360
I never met anyone as talented
and as dangerous as your mother.

445
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:41,360
Yeah, she fools me all the time.

446
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:45,080
If she knew about this, I’m sure
she would just do what she always does.

447
00:29:45,080 --> 00:29:47,160
I really hate your mother, you know?

448
00:29:48,280 --> 00:29:49,360
Who doesn’t?

449
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:52,280
Well, you.

450
00:29:59,280 --> 00:30:00,520
Come on in.

451
00:30:03,960 --> 00:30:05,040
Excuse me.

452
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:07,040
Come in.

453
00:30:07,040 --> 00:30:08,320
-Make yourself at home, love.
-Yes.

454
00:30:15,760 --> 00:30:17,000
ISSARA PREECHAJIT

455
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:21,280
Oh.

456
00:30:23,640 --> 00:30:26,160
You also like the Honnomo plushies?

457
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:28,560
Wait, but…

458
00:30:30,320 --> 00:30:32,120
I’ve never seen this model before.

459
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:34,920
Oh.

460
00:30:35,720 --> 00:30:36,760
It’s a knock-off.

461
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:39,400
My mother bought it for me.

462
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:42,280
She found it at the mall
and didn’t know it was a knock-off.

463
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:47,800
Old ladies, am I right?

464
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:48,680
How was I to know?

465
00:30:49,800 --> 00:30:53,880
I wanted to buy a new one
now that I make my own money,

466
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:55,120
the real thing, as well.

467
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:58,080
But then, I realized I don’t want it anymore.

468
00:31:02,520 --> 00:31:03,920
You have to see this.

469
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:04,880
This is unmissable.

470
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:06,320
Look at these, love.

471
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:07,240
This is adorable.

472
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:08,640
This is his childhood photo album.

473
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:10,400
See how chubby his cheeks are?

474
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:14,360
I’ve never seen U open up to anyone before.

475
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:21,000
But you, North, makes him believe in love at first sight.

476
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:22,920
Mom.

477
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:24,120
You’re embarrassing me.

478
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:28,400
Oh.

479
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:30,000
I ordered some snacks.

480
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:31,400
I’ll go get them.

481
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:32,320
Of course.

482
00:31:36,320 --> 00:31:37,560
What was that?

483
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:39,000
It slipped out.

484
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:40,040
Breathe!

485
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:41,520
Okay.

486
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:44,080
Uh…

487
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:46,480
Guys.

488
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,080
My name is Nart.

489
00:31:58,480 --> 00:31:59,160
I am—

490
00:31:59,160 --> 00:31:59,880
Auntie!

491
00:31:59,880 --> 00:32:00,600
Aunt Nart.

492
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:03,520
She’s my aunt.

493
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:04,400
Auntie.

494
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:05,640
That’s right.

495
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:06,360
His Aunt.

496
00:32:06,960 --> 00:32:07,640
I see.

497
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:08,960
Hello, Aunt Nart.

498
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:10,680
Hello.

499
00:32:26,240 --> 00:32:27,600
What are you doing here, Mom?

500
00:32:28,040 --> 00:32:29,240
What are you planning?

501
00:32:31,760 --> 00:32:32,360
I…

502
00:32:33,040 --> 00:32:36,200
I heard you’re quitting because
you’re getting married to someone.

503
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:42,080
I just wanted to see
what kind of person had won you over.

504
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:49,560
Congratulations.

505
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:55,400
You’ll finally have a place to call home.

506
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:01,560
I’m sorry

507
00:33:02,480 --> 00:33:04,760
I couldn’t do a better job at raising you.

508
00:33:07,960 --> 00:33:09,760
I’m really happy for you.

509
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:26,720
Do you…

510
00:33:27,720 --> 00:33:29,080
have a place to stay?

511
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:32,600
Don’t worry.

512
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:35,680
I’ll find some room to rent for the night.

513
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:39,600
You can stay at my place.

514
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:41,080
I’ll give you a ride.

515
00:34:07,320 --> 00:34:08,360
Let’s begin.

516
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:10,160
Give me your hand.

517
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:17,960
A strong fate.

518
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:20,480
You are destined for great things.

519
00:34:20,680 --> 00:34:23,000
But you must be wary of
who you surround yourself with,

520
00:34:23,400 --> 00:34:27,080
since people are drawn to you
to take advantage of you.

521
00:34:28,640 --> 00:34:30,840
This is especially true during this time.

522
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:37,440
He must be talking about U.

523
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:39,080
Definitely.

524
00:34:39,360 --> 00:34:40,360
Very possible.

525
00:34:42,520 --> 00:34:43,360
Your hand.

526
00:34:51,880 --> 00:34:52,680
What happened?

527
00:34:53,600 --> 00:34:54,640
You look alarmed.

528
00:34:59,320 --> 00:35:00,880
They are soulmates.

529
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:03,600
They have been soulmates in every lifetime.

530
00:35:04,840 --> 00:35:06,920
Though they don’t always end up together in all of them.

531
00:35:07,120 --> 00:35:08,880
But in every lifetime, they always find each other.

532
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:12,400
In this one, though…

533
00:35:15,680 --> 00:35:17,160
They will face a grand obstacle.

534
00:35:17,680 --> 00:35:19,080
If they’re able to get through the hurdle,

535
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:20,280
their love will be very strong.

536
00:35:21,560 --> 00:35:23,360
But if they fail to do so,

537
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:26,560
the paths will diverge for good.

538
00:35:27,240 --> 00:35:28,960
But we’ve never even fought.

539
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:30,000
Are you sure you were reading the right line?

540
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:30,560
Pai!

541
00:35:31,240 --> 00:35:32,640
How could you say that to Master?

542
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:36,600
Master.

543
00:35:36,840 --> 00:35:40,800
When is the best time for them to get married?

544
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:46,160
In four months.

545
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:48,040
That is the most auspicious.

546
00:35:48,440 --> 00:35:50,240
So in the middle of the year?

547
00:35:51,200 --> 00:35:55,600
Oh, but we’re opening a new branch
abroad during that time.

548
00:35:55,600 --> 00:35:58,760
We have Halloween, Christmas,
and the New Year at the end of the year.

549
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:01,480
At the beginning of next year, there’s Lunar
New Year, Valentine’s, and Songkran.

550
00:36:01,640 --> 00:36:05,640
With that alone, we’re already
more than a year behind.

551
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:07,360
When is my day off?

552
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:11,640
Your only days off are the 13th through to the 15th…

553
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:13,320
of next month.

554
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:22,960
How about this?

555
00:36:23,440 --> 00:36:28,000
We’ll pick the most auspicious day
between the 13th and 15th of next month.

556
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:29,120
That sounds good.

557
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:30,080
We’ll do that.

558
00:36:30,440 --> 00:36:31,360
We will not!

559
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:33,800
Master will find you the perfect day.

560
00:36:34,160 --> 00:36:38,840
Remember that our family is only here
because of Master’s great guidance.

561
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:42,080
So the fact that I work hard to the point of
having only three days off this year

562
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:43,440
means nothing, then?

563
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:46,280
I just want to get married on my terms.

564
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:47,640
Is that too much to ask?

565
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:48,920
I’m literally helping you.

566
00:36:49,560 --> 00:36:51,640
I think this is it for today.

567
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:54,400
Pai and I will talk about this.

568
00:36:56,320 --> 00:36:57,600
How arrogant of them.

569
00:36:58,240 --> 00:36:59,280
Do whatever you want, then!

570
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:03,960
Nana.

571
00:37:04,440 --> 00:37:04,800
Yes?

572
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:09,520
Sir?

573
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,600
Don’t forget about what I told you to look into.

574
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:15,400
I won’t, sir.

575
00:37:36,120 --> 00:37:37,480
You can’t even take one more step, love?

576
00:37:38,080 --> 00:37:39,000
No, I can not.

577
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:39,960
I’m so exhausted.

578
00:37:40,600 --> 00:37:42,480
Why does everything have to be so difficult?

579
00:37:49,720 --> 00:37:51,400
Is it a bad day for you, baby?

580
00:37:51,720 --> 00:37:52,440
So bad.

581
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:55,160
Alright. Wait right here.

582
00:38:40,760 --> 00:38:41,720
Medium rare, per usual?

583
00:38:53,600 --> 00:38:53,920
Baby.

584
00:38:55,160 --> 00:38:58,040
How did you know watching you cook
makes me feel at ease?

585
00:38:59,400 --> 00:38:59,960
I don’t know that.

586
00:39:01,040 --> 00:39:02,600
I just want to make you something delicious.

587
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:14,600
If marriage really was between two people,
that would be nice.

588
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:17,000
I want to get married right now.

589
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:18,120
Like North did?

590
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:23,280
I’m joking.

591
00:39:25,160 --> 00:39:27,680
I’ll have the bath running after dinner.

592
00:39:28,080 --> 00:39:29,280
We can try that new bath bomb.

593
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:31,960
Let’s take a bath together?

594
00:40:17,240 --> 00:40:20,440
You know, Mom,

595
00:40:20,720 --> 00:40:22,200
you can actually stay as long as you want.

596
00:40:23,160 --> 00:40:25,200
You know I can’t stay put too long.

597
00:40:26,360 --> 00:40:31,160
I mean, those cops still found me even
when I was moving around so much.

598
00:40:33,320 --> 00:40:35,720
You don’t need to work anymore, Mom.

599
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:38,720
I can take care of you.

600
00:40:40,480 --> 00:40:44,000
You can just have this room.

601
00:40:54,560 --> 00:40:56,400
You still like that thing?

602
00:41:02,280 --> 00:41:02,600
Yes.

603
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:10,200
Well, it was the last thing you gave me.

604
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:13,360
I have to keep it.

605
00:41:15,560 --> 00:41:20,960
You told me to exchange some receipt for my birthday gift at the mall.

606
00:41:24,280 --> 00:41:25,520
That thing is what I got.

607
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:31,520
When I came home, you were gone.

608
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:38,200
I’m sorry.

609
00:42:22,560 --> 00:42:23,240
What?

610
00:42:42,880 --> 00:42:43,680
Crap.

611
00:42:44,400 --> 00:42:45,280
Damn it!

612
00:42:59,680 --> 00:43:01,280
It was my fault for trusting her.

613
00:43:02,040 --> 00:43:03,440
People are nothing but selfish.

614
00:43:07,240 --> 00:43:09,000
Don’t think that.

615
00:43:09,280 --> 00:43:10,680
There are good people out there.

616
00:43:11,160 --> 00:43:14,400
You know, I myself have let so many of my targets go.

617
00:43:16,400 --> 00:43:17,000
You?

618
00:43:18,360 --> 00:43:18,680
It’s just…

619
00:43:20,280 --> 00:43:23,520
I think some people, if they weren’t unfortunate enough to meet the likes of us,

620
00:43:24,040 --> 00:43:26,680
are good people who can make the world a better place.

621
00:43:38,280 --> 00:43:41,880
How can you tell who those people are?

622
00:43:43,120 --> 00:43:45,040
You’ll know when you meet them.

623
00:43:46,680 --> 00:43:49,560
You can tell when someone is incapable of hurting anyone,

624
00:43:50,920 --> 00:43:53,760
and you can’t help feeling bad for hurting them.

625
00:43:57,960 --> 00:44:00,560
Even someone of your calibre went through something like that?

626
00:44:02,240 --> 00:44:04,400
That’s why we set up the rule:

627
00:44:05,400 --> 00:44:07,320
Don’t fall in love with the target.

628
00:44:36,600 --> 00:44:37,080
What are you doing?

629
00:44:37,160 --> 00:44:37,720
Oh!

630
00:44:38,960 --> 00:44:40,280
You said you were going to stay at your place.

631
00:44:42,480 --> 00:44:43,280
What are you doing, North?

632
00:44:44,440 --> 00:44:45,800
I’m not doing anything.

633
00:44:49,640 --> 00:44:50,280
U—

634
00:44:56,720 --> 00:44:57,240
What’s this?

635
00:44:59,280 --> 00:44:59,760
Open it.

636
00:45:04,480 --> 00:45:05,760
Surprise!

637
00:45:13,200 --> 00:45:15,480
I got you this plushie since you said you wanted it

638
00:45:17,320 --> 00:45:18,320
…as an apology.

639
00:45:20,520 --> 00:45:21,080
Apology?

640
00:45:23,960 --> 00:45:26,360
Your family is so nice to me.

641
00:45:27,240 --> 00:45:28,920
My family is awful to you.

642
00:45:30,080 --> 00:45:34,920
So I thought I want to be extra nice to you to make up for that.

643
00:45:42,120 --> 00:45:43,240
It’s authentic, you know?

644
00:45:59,400 --> 00:46:01,480
U, what’s wrong?

645
00:46:03,720 --> 00:46:04,200
It’s just…

646
00:46:05,480 --> 00:46:06,520
The real one

647
00:46:08,480 --> 00:46:09,200
…is beautiful.

648
00:46:14,600 --> 00:46:15,440
Thank you, North.

649
00:46:17,840 --> 00:46:18,720
Thank you.

650
00:46:20,480 --> 00:46:21,240
Of course.

651
00:46:21,480 --> 00:46:22,120
It’s nothing.

652
00:46:25,880 --> 00:46:27,040
If I knew you’d like it this much,

653
00:46:27,800 --> 00:46:29,080
I’d have bought ten more.

654
00:46:49,880 --> 00:46:51,040
Why did you want to meet me here?

655
00:46:54,120 --> 00:46:58,720
You said this suspicious U guy took North to his family home in Sathon, right?

656
00:47:09,880 --> 00:47:13,760
The estate agent turns a blind eye and rents this place out to scammers.

657
00:47:14,800 --> 00:47:16,760
Many of my clients have rented it.

658
00:47:17,240 --> 00:47:21,080
I asked the agent if it was rented recently.

659
00:47:28,360 --> 00:47:29,160
And it was.

660
00:47:30,520 --> 00:47:33,360
If he really was here, there must be something left inside.

661
00:48:04,200 --> 00:48:05,400
You want to talk to me?

662
00:48:07,360 --> 00:48:09,880
Stop renting that house in Sathon.

663
00:48:10,360 --> 00:48:11,680
It’s overused.

664
00:48:13,840 --> 00:48:14,520
What are you talking about?

665
00:48:31,480 --> 00:48:34,160
If you know that much, I don’t think we’re all that different.

666
00:48:34,560 --> 00:48:36,840
Let’s talk as people in the same line of work, shall we?

667
00:48:38,080 --> 00:48:39,400
What the hell do you think you’re doing?

668
00:48:41,320 --> 00:48:42,240
Exactly the same crap you’re pulling.

669
00:48:43,440 --> 00:48:43,880
Be respectful.

670
00:48:45,080 --> 00:48:46,240
I’m older.

671
00:48:46,840 --> 00:48:47,880
I’m also your in-law.

672
00:48:49,360 --> 00:48:49,840
Fine.

673
00:48:50,800 --> 00:48:51,400
Respect, it is.

674
00:48:53,600 --> 00:48:57,480
Let’s say, if you stay out of my way, I’ll stay out of yours.

675
00:48:59,840 --> 00:49:01,120
You watch my back.

676
00:49:02,440 --> 00:49:03,480
I’ll watch your back.

677
00:49:04,560 --> 00:49:05,840
And we can be on the same turf.

678
00:49:09,040 --> 00:49:09,400
Fine.

679
00:49:11,240 --> 00:49:12,400
I don’t trust you, though.

680
00:49:13,000 --> 00:49:13,680
Neither do I.

681
00:49:30,120 --> 00:49:31,280
Who is that for?

682
00:49:33,560 --> 00:49:36,040
It’s a gift basket for Mr. North.

683
00:49:37,000 --> 00:49:37,320
What?

684
00:49:39,680 --> 00:49:41,880
I’m sure U doesn’t love North.

685
00:49:42,920 --> 00:49:43,880
I just need evidence.

686
00:49:57,280 --> 00:49:58,560
You’re gonna bug them?

687
00:49:59,200 --> 00:50:00,400
Don’t you think this is too much, Pai?

688
00:50:00,480 --> 00:50:03,480
This is nothing compared to the airtags in the bags
that are their wedding gift, sir.

689
00:50:07,560 --> 00:50:08,000
Pai.

690
00:50:11,240 --> 00:50:12,760
If he proves to be trustworthy,

691
00:50:13,400 --> 00:50:14,640
I’ll leave them alone.

692
00:50:15,320 --> 00:50:16,480
I just need to be sure first.

693
00:50:44,960 --> 00:50:45,640
(Code Red!)

694
00:50:53,600 --> 00:50:54,360
It’s okay, U.

695
00:50:54,640 --> 00:50:55,040
I’ll get it.

696
00:50:56,160 --> 00:50:56,480
Okay.

697
00:51:07,720 --> 00:51:10,120
Who does Pai want me to give this to now?

698
00:51:11,600 --> 00:51:12,600
That’s not the case, sir.

699
00:51:12,800 --> 00:51:16,920
This gift basket is for you to congratulate you on your newlywed life.

700
00:51:18,280 --> 00:51:18,920
“Congratulate” me?

701
00:51:18,920 --> 00:51:19,440
Yes.

702
00:51:21,560 --> 00:51:22,480
He’s right across the hall.

703
00:51:22,880 --> 00:51:24,160
Why isn’t he here to “congratulate” me himself?

704
00:51:26,440 --> 00:51:27,800
Oh.

705
00:51:28,160 --> 00:51:30,960
Pai is currently very busy.

706
00:51:31,040 --> 00:51:36,760
He feels that his initial reaction was exaggerated by his surprise,

707
00:51:36,880 --> 00:51:39,120
but he’s okay with it now.

708
00:51:39,400 --> 00:51:42,920
May I come in and place the gift basket inside for you, sir?

709
00:51:43,680 --> 00:51:43,920
Sure.

710
00:51:43,920 --> 00:51:45,240
Oh, no need.

711
00:51:45,880 --> 00:51:47,760
This looks gorgeous.

712
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:49,000
I’ll take it from here.

713
00:51:49,760 --> 00:51:50,960
This, too?

714
00:51:52,440 --> 00:51:53,360
Oh, she wouldn’t let go.

715
00:51:54,760 --> 00:51:55,280
Let me help.

716
00:51:55,280 --> 00:51:55,800
Right.

717
00:51:56,280 --> 00:51:57,320
Send our gratitude to Mr. Pai.

718
00:51:57,320 --> 00:51:57,800
Of course.

719
00:51:57,800 --> 00:51:58,480
Thank you.

720
00:51:58,800 --> 00:51:59,680
Do you need my help with that?

721
00:51:59,760 --> 00:52:00,520
It’s alright, Nana.

722
00:52:01,160 --> 00:52:01,800
Thank you.

723
00:52:02,200 --> 00:52:03,240
I am more than happy to—

724
00:52:11,360 --> 00:52:11,760
That was weird.

725
00:52:13,360 --> 00:52:14,040
Super weird.

726
00:52:15,880 --> 00:52:16,800
I don’t think so.

727
00:52:17,600 --> 00:52:19,880
Maybe Pai really is happy for us.

728
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:23,320
Oh, matching bags.

729
00:52:24,680 --> 00:52:25,440
Let me see.

730
00:52:26,800 --> 00:52:27,440
We can match.

731
00:52:38,200 --> 00:52:38,840
What’s wrong, U?

732
00:52:39,560 --> 00:52:40,960
I think the zipper’s stuck.

733
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:43,120
Can you help me with it?

734
00:52:43,240 --> 00:52:43,800
Let me see.

735
00:53:04,800 --> 00:53:05,400
An airtag?

736
00:53:09,120 --> 00:53:11,400
I guess Pai doesn’t want us to lose the bags, huh?

737
00:53:18,280 --> 00:53:19,200
Oh, sorry.

738
00:53:20,000 --> 00:53:20,880
It’s alright.

739
00:53:21,040 --> 00:53:21,800
I’ll pick it up.

740
00:53:36,840 --> 00:53:38,600
Pai, you jerk!

741
00:53:44,880 --> 00:53:45,880
Tim, where is Pai?

742
00:53:47,240 --> 00:53:47,840
Uh…

743
00:53:55,680 --> 00:53:56,720
What do you think you’re doing?

744
00:53:57,840 --> 00:53:59,760
This is so disrespectful to me and my husband!

745
00:54:03,680 --> 00:54:04,520
I’m worried about you.

746
00:54:05,160 --> 00:54:06,280
You don’t know who he is.

747
00:54:06,800 --> 00:54:08,360
How can you love him?

748
00:54:08,840 --> 00:54:11,920
U and I are not inmates that need to be under constant surveillance.

749
00:54:14,320 --> 00:54:15,440
What will you have me do?

750
00:54:15,720 --> 00:54:16,800
Nothing!

751
00:54:17,000 --> 00:54:17,760
It’s my life!

752
00:54:17,800 --> 00:54:20,360
It’s your life, but it’s my responsibility.

753
00:54:20,960 --> 00:54:23,560
If anything happens to you, they will blame me.

754
00:54:25,880 --> 00:54:26,640
They will blame you?

755
00:54:27,480 --> 00:54:29,360
So you’re just trying to save your own butt?

756
00:54:31,240 --> 00:54:35,000
Honestly, Pai, do you ever care how I feel?

757
00:54:36,200 --> 00:54:37,160
Don’t say that.

758
00:54:37,160 --> 00:54:38,080
Why can’t I?

759
00:54:39,240 --> 00:54:40,440
You can leave me alone now.

760
00:54:41,400 --> 00:54:45,160
My life would be absolutely perfect without you in it.

761
00:54:58,240 --> 00:54:58,920
I’m done.

762
00:54:59,120 --> 00:54:59,920
- North.
- Let’s go, U.

763
00:54:59,920 --> 00:55:00,840
- Calm down.
- U, come on.

764
00:55:00,840 --> 00:55:01,640
- Talk to him nicely.
- U.

765
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:03,360
North. North.

766
00:55:21,320 --> 00:55:21,680
Pai.

767
00:55:21,800 --> 00:55:22,640
I want to be alone right now.

768
00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:29,600
There’s no way I can let that happen.

769
00:55:29,720 --> 00:55:30,240
Come here.

770
00:55:49,360 --> 00:55:50,960
I’m never talking to Pai again.

771
00:55:51,640 --> 00:55:53,680
And he’s not allowed to talk to me, either!

772
00:55:55,280 --> 00:55:56,600
I’m sure he’s just worried about you.

773
00:55:58,360 --> 00:56:00,160
But don’t you think that was too much, U?

774
00:56:00,600 --> 00:56:03,800
Pai treats me like I’m his pet dog.

775
00:56:04,520 --> 00:56:06,320
Might as well just get me a microchip.

776
00:56:09,080 --> 00:56:10,160
Why are you laughing?

777
00:56:10,360 --> 00:56:11,560
I’m boiling!

778
00:56:12,640 --> 00:56:14,040
You’re adorable when you’re angry.

779
00:56:15,200 --> 00:56:17,560
Pai must have raised you really well.

780
00:56:19,160 --> 00:56:20,800
U, that’s not funny.

781
00:56:21,280 --> 00:56:23,200
Alright, I’m not teasing you anymore.

782
00:56:24,840 --> 00:56:26,200
What are you gonna do now?

783
00:56:26,280 --> 00:56:27,120
Can I talk to you?

784
00:56:27,960 --> 00:56:28,560
Tim.

785
00:56:30,760 --> 00:56:31,280
Alright.

786
00:56:31,640 --> 00:56:33,760
But we talk here, in front of U.

787
00:56:41,720 --> 00:56:42,520
Please, do me a favor.

788
00:56:43,960 --> 00:56:45,160
Will you apologize to Pai?

789
00:56:46,160 --> 00:56:46,840
No.

790
00:56:47,400 --> 00:56:48,320
I didn’t do anything wrong.

791
00:56:48,800 --> 00:56:51,120
If that was all, excuse me.

792
00:56:51,320 --> 00:56:51,800
North.

793
00:56:53,760 --> 00:56:54,880
I am begging you.

794
00:56:56,280 --> 00:56:58,960
He… Pai is miserable.

795
00:56:59,400 --> 00:57:00,640
He refuses to eat.

796
00:57:01,240 --> 00:57:02,880
I’ve never seen him like this before.

797
00:57:10,600 --> 00:57:12,560
Pai cares about you a lot.

798
00:57:13,280 --> 00:57:14,720
I don’t know what to say to him.

799
00:57:16,120 --> 00:57:17,400
Can you, please, talk to him?

800
00:57:18,800 --> 00:57:20,160
Is he really in such bad shape?

801
00:57:25,760 --> 00:57:26,320
Pai!

802
00:57:27,080 --> 00:57:27,440
Hey.

803
00:57:31,160 --> 00:57:32,280
Got caught up, did you?

804
00:57:33,480 --> 00:57:34,320
Like hell I did.

805
00:58:01,800 --> 00:58:02,320
Pai.

806
00:58:06,760 --> 00:58:08,680
Are you sad because of what I said?

807
00:58:20,320 --> 00:58:22,240
I’m sorry!

808
00:58:22,240 --> 00:58:24,600
I didn’t mean to!

809
00:58:25,200 --> 00:58:26,680
Are you not mad at me anymore?

810
00:58:26,680 --> 00:58:28,520
How could I be mad at you?

811
00:58:53,880 --> 00:58:54,480
Goodnight, Pai.

812
00:58:54,960 --> 00:58:55,520
Bye, Tim.

813
00:59:17,200 --> 00:59:17,520
Baby.

814
00:59:19,120 --> 00:59:20,400
What did you say to North?

815
00:59:21,360 --> 00:59:22,800
He’s usually very stubborn,

816
00:59:23,480 --> 00:59:24,920
but he easily apologized this time.

817
00:59:27,640 --> 00:59:29,960
All it takes is telling them you’re sad and it gets everyone in a panic.

818
00:59:30,400 --> 00:59:30,920
No way.

819
00:59:32,040 --> 00:59:32,760
Really.

820
00:59:35,480 --> 00:59:37,200
Well, when you’re sad, it’s…

821
00:59:45,280 --> 00:59:45,760
What is it?

822
00:59:48,360 --> 00:59:49,080
It’s funny.

823
00:59:51,120 --> 00:59:53,000
You make a face like a little duckling when you’re sad.

824
00:59:53,840 --> 00:59:54,760
Duckling?

825
00:59:55,600 --> 00:59:56,200
Yeah.

826
00:59:57,520 --> 00:59:59,880
Don’t be sad again, you hear me?

827
01:00:01,160 --> 01:00:01,720
There.

828
01:00:02,720 --> 01:00:03,600
What was that for?

829
01:00:04,240 --> 01:00:05,440
You called me a little duckling.

830
01:00:06,320 --> 01:00:07,400
You really look like one.

831
01:00:08,000 --> 01:00:08,560
Watch it!

832
01:00:09,240 --> 01:00:10,080
I’m not talking to you anymore!

833
01:00:10,160 --> 01:00:10,520
Baby!

834
01:00:10,520 --> 01:00:11,480
Come back here!

835
01:00:13,000 --> 01:00:13,640
What?

836
01:00:15,480 --> 01:00:16,320
Where are you going?

837
01:00:17,280 --> 01:00:18,720
I didn’t do anything.

838
01:00:20,840 --> 01:00:21,800
You hit me?

839
01:00:21,800 --> 01:00:23,000
You won’t catch me!

840
01:00:23,600 --> 01:00:24,440
Stop it.

841
01:00:28,080 --> 01:00:28,720
Do you surrender?

842
01:00:28,720 --> 01:00:29,200
Alright!

843
01:00:29,200 --> 01:00:29,920
You do?

844
01:00:52,360 --> 01:00:54,480
I would like to invite you to dinner at home, Mr. Pai.

845
01:00:54,960 --> 01:00:56,000
Please, come in.

846
01:00:57,800 --> 01:00:59,280
Help me in the kitchen, then.

847
01:01:00,440 --> 01:01:01,720
How are you in love already?

848
01:01:02,160 --> 01:01:02,920
You just met.

849
01:01:04,880 --> 01:01:06,080
Did it take you and Pai

850
01:01:06,960 --> 01:01:08,400
a long time to fall in love?

851
01:01:10,120 --> 01:01:11,360
You’re blushing.

852
01:01:11,600 --> 01:01:12,960
This is like when we first started dating.

853
01:01:13,480 --> 01:01:17,200
I just happened to see the side of him that makes me feel protective over.

854
01:01:17,200 --> 01:01:18,800
It feels like I just got to know another part of you.

855
01:01:20,440 --> 01:01:21,120
I like it.

